INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'b6c37b59-75fe-4de0-9edf-076d53f5466d',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$DVC Pipelines in CI/CD — Automated Retraining with Evaluation Gates$escape$,
  $escape$DVC's `dvc repro` is the backbone of ML CI/CD. When a GitHub Actions workflow triggers on data or code changes, `dvc repro` reruns only the invalidated stages defined in `dvc.yaml` — skipping cached stages automatically via content-addressed storage.

The critical piece is the evaluation gate. After `dvc repro`, use `dvc metrics show` and `dvc metrics diff` to compare metrics against the baseline commit. A custom Python script or `dvc params diff` can assert thresholds — block the pipeline if `val/f1` drops below 0.85, for example.

For deployment, gate on `dvc push` only after the metric check passes. Tag the Git commit with `dvc tag` and push the model artifact to your DVC remote (S3, Azure Blob, GCS). The downstream deploy job pulls the exact artifact via `dvc pull` using the tagged commit ref, guaranteeing reproducibility.

Use `dvc studio` or parse `dvclive` logs for experiment tracking across runs — giving you a full audit trail of every retrain without storing large binaries in Git.$escape$,
  $escape$# .github/workflows/ml-pipeline.yml (key steps)
- name: Reproduce pipeline
  run: dvc repro

- name: Check evaluation gate
  run: |
    python evaluate_gate.py --metric val/f1 --threshold 0.85
  # evaluate_gate.py reads dvc metrics show --json

- name: Push artifacts if gate passes
  run: |
    dvc push
    git tag "model-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)"
    git push --tags

- name: Deploy — pull exact artifact by tag
  run: dvc pull --run-cache$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
