INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '12f27d23-3e53-49ca-8824-421313062a5b',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$DVC Model Registry — Champion/Challenger, Shadow Deployment & Canary Releases$escape$,
  $escape$DVC's model registry makes champion/challenger testing auditable without a separate registry service. Tag your production model as `champion` and the candidate as `challenger` using `dvc artifacts tag add`, then pull both into your serving environment independently with `dvc artifacts get`.

For shadow deployment, wire the challenger into a dedicated `dvc.yaml` stage with log-only semantics — it receives mirrored inference requests but its outputs never reach users. Emit shadow metrics via the `metrics:` key in that stage, then compare with `dvc metrics diff main exp-canary-v2` to evaluate without bias.

Canary releases map cleanly to `params.yaml`. Define a `traffic_split` float there and reference it in your serving stage command. Increment it in steps — 5 %, 20 %, 50 % — running `dvc repro` at each threshold to regenerate metric artifacts. Gate full promotion on `dvc metrics show`: if the challenger's held-out metric (e.g., F1 or NDCG) clears your threshold, a single `dvc artifacts tag add champion` atomically promotes it. Every tag move is git-backed, giving you a full rollback path via `dvc artifacts tag add champion --rev <prev-sha>`.$escape$,
  $escape$# Tag production model and candidate in DVC model registry
dvc artifacts tag add champion models/classifier --rev main
dvc artifacts tag add challenger models/classifier --rev exp-canary-v2

# Pull both into shadow-serving environment
dvc artifacts get . models/classifier --tag champion -o models/champion/
dvc artifacts get . models/classifier --tag challenger -o models/challenger/

# Diff held-out metrics between the two git revisions
dvc metrics diff main exp-canary-v2

# Promote challenger to champion after shadow validation
dvc artifacts tag add champion models/classifier --rev exp-canary-v2$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
